						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify;  background-color: #000016;   background-image: none;  background-repeat: repeat-x; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<P><FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ffffff size=3>Disappointed with SOE</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT></FONT></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P><FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ffffff size=3>First a disclaimer:<SPAN></SPAN>Most of my gripes here are from posts I’ve read.<SPAN></SPAN>As I usually just read the top couple of posts in any thread and then skim the rest.<SPAN></SPAN>I’m hoping, not expecting, someone can prove me wrong and share the good news.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT></FONT></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P><I><SPAN><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff>Is there really any good reason to play a bard past level 65 any more?</FONT></FONT></SPAN></I></P>
<P><FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ffffff size=3>Asking this as it looks like SOE has in one way or another <I>decreased</I> (See the rizlona’s line of spells past level 65 bards song abilities while <I>increasing</I> other classes abilities.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff><FONT size=3><SPAN></SPAN>SOE’s line of reasoning for this is that if they keep the focus effect of our rizlona line of songs as it is at 65 or increase it at higher levels it becomes game unbalancing.&nbsp; <SPAN></SPAN>I can sort of understand the reason for this.&nbsp; <SPAN></SPAN>Just have one question I’d like SOE to answer or anyone else that might have more game knowledge.&nbsp; <EM>How is it more unbalancing then adding a wizard?&nbsp; </EM></FONT><FONT size=3>I know another wizard won’t bring the party overhaste, mana regen, and DS, but their increased DPS from their nukes will more then make up for it.&nbsp; <SPAN></SPAN>Or any other class as I just tossed out a wizard as a example.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff><SPAN></SPAN>For a long time Bards effectiveness in EQ was what we brought to increase the party/raids effectiveness with&nbsp;our songs.<SPAN></SPAN>With the OoW expansion we took a massive decrease in our abilities to increase the parties DPS without any real increase in other areas.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff><SPAN><FONT size=3>&nbsp;So why would a party/</FONT></SPAN><I><SPAN>raid be willing to invite that Bard into a party/raid when you can invite another class?&nbsp; </SPAN></I><FONT size=3><SPAN></SPAN>I know there’s been plenty of threads out there already with posts on the diminish returns high level bards are bringing to the end raid content.<SPAN></SPAN>From my opinion, OoW looks like it’s trying to kill off the bards as a class in EQ as there is no real increase in a bards power here.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff><SPAN></SPAN>I’m hoping more knowledgeable people out there can posts examples of why this is true, or even if untrue.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT></FONT></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff><SPAN></SPAN>But what I think <I>really irks me</I> was the post where we had people wanting to know if these songs were going live and we kept getting told they was PH for our new songs which was still being worked on.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT></FONT></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P><FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ffffff size=3>To show how sad I am at the state of bards.<SPAN></SPAN>When I get home tonight I’m going hit the cancel button on my renewal button for my account.<SPAN></SPAN>If for some reason I completely misunderstood what happened in the OoW expansion and I hear good news I’ll then reactivate my account.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT></FONT></FONT>&nbsp;</P><SPAN><FONT color=#ffffff>Thanks for listening to my gripes</FONT></SPAN></DIV>
																		
