									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 217 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_5.gif' border=0 alt='1 rating - 5.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Well, I am very dissapointed at the way they changed the PbAoE songs for bards too.<BR></DIV>
<DIV>It's not like I don't see the problem, I have a 65 bard and I could kite up to 35 mobs at once in certain zones (not more because i would get lag). I could get away with it if I did everything right. If not, then i am dead. That's the way I played my bard, and i really liked it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But I do understand that this can be very unfair. When there are other players around, unsocial and selfish bards can pull way too many mobs at once, leaving little or nothing for other players. So the fact that bards can pull a massive number of mobs and kite them with their PbAoE songs, and that it would/could/should be nerfed, is not something that i disagree with.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's just the way it is done. There is absolutly no sense in the fact that, when i am in a group fighting two mobs, and one mob starts running, my AoE songs suddently stop working! The same situation applies when the mob is feared, or when a groupmate runs away to get aggro, it is completely UNunderstandable.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And it's not like there are no other ways to solve this problem. I dont mean to say that people didnt think this over very carefully (I still hope to think they did), but there are other ways to "tune down" the swarm abilities of a bard.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For example, maximize the number of mobs that a bard PbAoE will hit. Wizards have spells that hit a max. number of 4 mobs, bards have spells that hit a max. number of 4 mobs (that dd that costs mana, remember?), so why not implement it for all PbAoE songs?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Or what about letting the PbAoE songs cost some mana? Bard have no real ways to recover mana quickly; mod rods, KEI and their own mana song all wont work, so even though a bard could use his PbAoE for a while, the downtime would make it less interesting for a bard to do so.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If Sony somehow decides to keep the PbAoE songs working as they do now (after the Oow patch), I am really considering giving up EQ at all, cancelling my two accounts.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thune - 65 bard - Stromm</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
																		
