						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>Not to rain on the parade guys, but the original post was about OoW.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And he was talking about how OoW isn't very good for bards. I understand that on <STRONG>top</STRONG> of all that is the AE nerf. But we are not only getting hit on one side of the face here, we are getting hit from the other side too. So here is one&nbsp;reason&nbsp;why people are cancelling thier account (because of - read the first post). While I am not at liberty to say, AE nerf is a small portion of what happening to us... the bigger picture unfolds. And its not pretty 
<HR>
</DIV>
<P>Don't think it's just bards that OOW was a let down for, I can't see anything to get excited about OOW at all. Nothing new has been added to the game it's just a rehash of old ideas. Maybe it's just me but the whole eq experience is just getting stale.</P>
<P>Sure we can get to level 70 but we are still dead in ten hits the same as at level one except now we don't have a chance of standing toe to toe solo&nbsp;with a&nbsp;dark blue&nbsp;mob and winning. (Con says a difficult encounter but you might win that doesn't seem right to me).</P>
<P>I just do not want to&nbsp;HAVE to group why does that cause a problem? Can we not decide how often we play solo?</P>
<P>We can get a different epic which just like the last one is going to be outdated in six months time when the next two expansions are out.</P>
<P>We do more damage but so do the mobs who also have stupid numbers of hit points or ridiculous regens. But hang on we have already killed the in-game gods so where do we go from there?</P>
<P>Unlike previous expansions up to and including LDON the expansions added new depth and variety to the gameplay GOD and now OOW seem to be more about limiting what people can do unless you are a cleric of course when you've never had it so good now you can put up lfg go away for 15mins and come back and select which group you are going to deign with your presence.</P>
<P>(Note to self must get over this anti-cleric thing :smileywink<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
																		
										</td></tr>
